/*! \page vertex Vertex Types

Real-time applications can often have different requirements when it comes to vertex data structures. Rather than waste memory, KSR provides several vertex structures and formats to KSR Applications.

\section structures Data Structures
The following data structures are available in KSR.
<UL>
<LI>VERTEX_DIFFUSE_TEX1</LI>
<LI>VERTEX_NORMAL_TEX1</LI>
<LI>VERTEX_NORMAL_DIFFUSE_TEX1</LI>
<LI>VERTEX_DIFFUSE_TEX2</LI>
<LI>VERTEX_NORMAL_TEX2</LI>
<LI>VERTEX_NORMAL_DIFFUSE_TEX2</LI>
<LI>VERTEX_POINT</LI>
</UL>

\section formats Flexible Vertex Formats
A Flexible Vertex Format (FVF) code describes the contents order of a vertex. It is necessary to provide KSR when required with a FVF code to describe the format of the vertex data you are using. Below are the FVF codes provided by KSR.
<UL>
<LI>FVF_DIFFUSE_TEX1</LI>
<LI>FVF_NORMAL_TEX1</LI>
<LI>FVF_NORMAL_DIFFUSE_TEX1</LI>
<LI>FVF_DIFFUSE_TEX2</LI>
<LI>FVF_NORMAL_TEX2</LI>
<LI>FVF_POINT</LI>
</UL>
*/